[SN]TITLE[SN]
Brighton home becomes work of art inspired by Michelangelo

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An amateur artist has spent 14 years painting every wall and ceiling of his terraced house in a style inspired by the Sistine Chapel and the works of Michelangelo.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
11 January 2017 Last updated at 11:33 GMT
Now Robert Burns has run out of walls and ceilings.
His artworks are starting to get smaller and smaller so he can still find space to hang them.
